I placed a phone order today, a simple sandwich and fries. They first said 15 minutes and then 10. I arrive 15 minutes and it looked as if he was cooking my order. The girl behind the counter asked how many sides of salad dressing I would want and showed me a small little container and said they would be $1 each. I declined the side dressing. When she rang my $9.25 sandwich up, she said it would be $10.25. I reminded her that I did not get a side dressing and she said that was tax. Mmmmmhhhh. Last I checked, tax on food in NYC is 8.75%. I asked about it and she feigned ignorance and said it was the computer that figured it out, not her. I asked her to check it again and for a printed out receipt and she gave me a hand written receipt with the $1 tax. I again asked for a print out from her computer that figured out this tax and she said she could not since it was her first day working there. I asked to speak with the manager and she said he was not there and did not know his name since, again, it was her first day. I asked the other girl, who all of a sudden did not speak English, who the manager is and she said Max and he was not in. They really need to realize that just because I have redhair and freckles, that there may be a slight chance that I also speak Spanish. So silly. I will not be returning due to their unethical practices. Either this “new” employee was pocketing the cash or they all round up on the tax on everyone’s meals so they can make a bit more profit. And funny that once she saw I was paying cash, the computer system could not print out a receipt and she had to hand write it. And also, the sandwich was mediocre at best. Get your act together, could be a cute neighborhood spot, but they lost my business as well as my coworkers.
